  "prompt": "Reptiles: How do you find a lost snake in your home?",
  "response": "Here are some tips for finding a lost snake in your home:\n\n1. Search carefully and methodically\n- Check warm, dark places like behind furniture, under appliances\n- Look in closets, behind baseboards, near heat sources\n- Check areas with potential hiding spots\n\n2. Practical search techniques\n- Turn off lights and use a flashlight\n- Snakes often seek warmth, so check near heat vents, electronics\n- Look in rooms with carpets, rugs, or clutter\n\n3. Create potential traps\n- Place a heating pad or warm hot water bottle in an area\n- Put out a small cardboard box with air holes\n- Use sticky traps designed for rodents (with caution)\n\n4. Signs to look for\n- Slight movement\n- Shed skin\n- Tracks or trails\n\n5. Additional recommendations\n- Keep other pets away from search areas\n- Remain calm\n- Consider professional help if you can't locate the snake\n\n6. Prevention for future\n- Secure enclosures\n- Check for potential escape routes\n- Address any gaps or holes in walls/floors\n\nSafety note: If it's a venomous snake, contact professional wildlife removal services immediately.",
